## 🔴 ISSUE 1 — CRITICAL: Wrong Base Package (Main Application Class)

**File:** `src/main/java/com/ticketing/ticketing_platform/TicketingPlatformApplication.java`

**Problem:** Spring Initializr generated the base package as `com.ticketing.ticketing_platform` (using the artifact ID). Every single document in the project — `intsructions.txt`, `copilot-instructions.md`, all 10 session prompts — mandates the base package be **exactly** `com.ticketing`. 

If left unfixed, when Copilot creates `com.ticketing.event.service.EventService`, Spring Boot's `@SpringBootApplication` component scan will NOT pick it up because it only scans `com.ticketing.ticketing_platform.*`. The app will start but all `@Service`, `@Repository`, and `@RestController` beans will be invisible to the Spring context.

**Fix:** Move the main class to the correct package.

---

## 🟡 ISSUE 2 — IMPORTANT: `application.yaml` is Essentially Empty

**File:** `src/main/resources/application.yaml`

**Problem:** The file contains only 3 lines (the app name). There is no datasource, Redis, or RabbitMQ configuration at all. When `./mvnw spring-boot:run` is executed, Spring Boot will fail immediately trying to auto-configure JPA without a datasource URL.

**The Day 1 prompt** correctly defines the `application-local.yml` profile config block (lines 199–215 of day-01), **but it doesn't yet exist as a file**. The `application.yaml` also needs a `spring.profiles.active` pointer entry so the AI knows which profile to activate during local dev.

**Fix:** Populate `application.yaml` with the profile pointer and create `application-local.yml`.

---

## 🟡 ISSUE 3 — IMPORTANT: Version Mismatch in `copilot-instructions.md`

**File:** `.github/copilot-instructions.md` line 9

**Problem:** 
```
Stack: Java 21, Spring Boot 3.x, PostgreSQL 15, Redis 7, RabbitMQ 3.12
```
The correct versions (as locked in `intsructions.txt` and all session prompts) are:
- PostgreSQL **17** (not 15)
- RabbitMQ **4.2.5** (not 3.12)

`copilot-instructions.md` is the file GitHub Copilot reads **on every single file** in the project. If it states wrong versions, Copilot will suggest wrong Testcontainers image tags (`postgres:15` instead of `postgres:17`) on any integration test it generates.

**Fix:** Update the stack line to match the locked versions.

---

## 🟡 ISSUE 4 — IMPORTANT: `intsructions.txt` and Day-01 Prompt Still Reference `qrgen:2.6.0`

**Files:**
- `intsructions.txt` line 114: `QR Code : ZXing via qrgen 2.6.0`
- `day-01-project-init.md` line 94: `Add to pom.xml manually: ... qrgen:2.6.0`

**Problem:** We replaced `qrgen` with `com.google.zxing:3.5.2` during this session because `qrgen` pulled the corrupted Apache Batik `xml-apis-ext-1.3.04.jar`. If these documents aren't updated, the AI being asked to run Day 1 will try to add `qrgen:2.6.0` back into the `pom.xml`, re-introducing the broken transitive dependency and breaking the build again.

**Fix:** Update both files to reference `com.google.zxing:core:3.5.2` and `com.google.zxing:javase:3.5.2`.

